    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c9a1e092_bd464e14",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-26T14:33:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Sure, do this because it’s what the library offers, but…\n\nIn general, I’m not so enthusiastic about the type hole that raw address getters like this open up. If the libraries are being made more sensible about these things, it’d be cool if fdio (or some slightly higher-level fdio wrapper) understood the smart pointers more natively, so that type holes like this wouldn’t be necessary, or at least wouldn’t need to be used in places like this.\n\nThere’s no action to take here right now. I’m just mentioning it because it’d be a library refactor along the lines of libzx, and you might know if something like this is planned (or might have better luck adding it to the plans, even).",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 56
      },
      "revId": "086ebd34af6e1eaf391202ffb2b600ce84ca57cf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1635f685_4b813ee7",
        "filename": "client/crashpad_client_fuchsia.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 102,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001385
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-27T12:19:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "fdio is a C API, so can\u0027t make use of the libzx containers (e.g. the first parameter would be passed a zx::job() in a C++ version).\n\nProviding a C++ wrapper for fdio in the same vein as libzx wrapping the syscalls does seem desirable - filed Fuchsia bug ZX-2422 for that.",
      "parentUuid": "c9a1e092_bd464e14",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 102,
        "startChar": 26,
        "endLine": 102,
        "endChar": 56
      },
