      "writtenOn": "2018-07-26T14:33:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I\u0027ve not changed the names of relevant classes from using Task to using more specific object types like Process or Thread, except where the APIs only make sense for the new more specific types, FWIW. Let me know if you think names like this should also be updated, though.\n\nThis kind of thing is confusing because if you read it, it’s not clear what it’s supposed to be operating on.\n\nIf this really can operate on more than just a thread, then is there a clearer way to express that using the type system?\n\nIf not, I think we should rename the function to keep things clear.",
      "parentUuid": "d9c459e5_d4c31344",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 33,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 33,
        "endChar": 14
      },
      "revId": "086ebd34af6e1eaf391202ffb2b600ce84ca57cf",
