    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d6c6b44a_2d47e3b8",
        "filename": "util/fuchsia/koid_utilities.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 88,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001385
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-24T21:17:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As noted previously, zx::object_base is the universal base-class for the handle containers. However, it provides no methods to work with the handles, so we have to re-wrap the underlying handle into an unowned_handle to work with it. Alternative would be to just revert to zx_object_get_info() below.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 88,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 88,
        "endChar": 48
      },
      "revId": "086ebd34af6e1eaf391202ffb2b600ce84ca57cf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e35b4f8c_efb531d3",
        "filename": "util/fuchsia/koid_utilities.cc",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 137,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001385
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-07-24T21:17:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Note that forcibly wrapping the result into a zx::thread is safe because |parent| is a zx::process, so can only have thread children.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 137,
        "startChar": 9,
        "endLine": 137,
        "endChar": 19
      },
      "revId": "086ebd34af6e1eaf391202ffb2b600ce84ca57cf",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d08f5363_a10015b8",
        "filename": "util/fuchsia/koid_utilities.cc",
