      "writtenOn": "2018-07-26T14:33:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Since zx::process and zx::thread are specializations of the zx::task\u003cT\u003e template we cannot just accept a zx::task\u003c\u003e here, so I\u0027ve overloaded the constructor, which has the benefit that we don\u0027t have to make a kernel call to query the type of the handle.\n\nGuess so. At first, I was going to suggest doing the overload outside, as a dual-personality SuspendTask(), and then making ScopedTaskSuspend() be a template wrapped around that. But that’s a little added complexity for minimal benefit, so this should be fine.",
